## 15.8c

The value of right is determined by subtracting the average price from the market value of the shares held by the shareholders. On the other hand, the average price of one share is computed by dividing the total amount of shares by the number of shares. This is computed as follows:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Value of right}&={\text{Market value of the shares -}}{{(}}\dfrac{\text{Total amount of shares}}{\text{Number of shares}} {{)}}
\end{aligned}$$
